Inaugural ARC Workshop

A full-day, practical workshop focused on building theranostics / targeted radiopharmaceutical therapy (TRT) readiness for community programs.

ARC Workshop #1
Theranostics: Foundation to Frontline
Date April 18, 2026

What to expect

ARC Workshop #1 combines foundational instruction with hands-on practice and team-based simulation. Content is designed for sites building or expanding theranostics services, with a focus on operational readiness and reliable workflows.

  • Morning: foundational lectures + panel on referral pathways and community readiness
  • Afternoon: hands-on rotations (prep/handling, imaging protocols, dosimetry practice)
  • Group simulation: coordinate a case from consult to follow-up, then debrief barriers/opportunities

Materials provided

  • ARC Core Curriculum (print + digital)
  • Sample TRT patient workflow protocols
  • ARC Online Learning Platform access
  • Pre- and post-training assessments
  • Workshop completion certificate (CME/CE credit)
